---
// V01StatusCallout — the "v0.1 STATUS" drench callout shared by /trust/
// and /why-verification/. Both pages need to clarify that today every
// submission lands at status: unverified, that the signed verifier is
// the submit-time gate, and that the trust-score promotion engine ships
// in M05.
//
// /trust/ also wants to point at the per-tier verifier-shape contract in
// runlog-docs §17.4. Pass `tierDetail` to include that extra sentence;
// /why-verification/ omits it because the surrounding section already
// spells out the verifier flow.
//
// Drench tint comes from `.callout.drench` in src/styles/global.css.

interface Props {
  /** Show the per-tier verifier-shape sentence (assertion_only / unit /
   *  integration / reexecute) plus the runlog-docs §17.4 pointer. Used
   *  on /trust/; omitted on /why-verification/. */
  tierDetail?: boolean;
}

const { tierDetail = false } = Astro.props;
---
<div class="callout drench" data-tag="V0.1 STATUS">
  Every v0.1 submission lands at <code>status: unverified</code>, signed
  bundle included. The signed verifier is still the submit-time gate:
  differential branch execution and mutation testing run locally inside
  the binary, and the server rejects invalid bundles with typed errors.
  {tierDetail && (
    <>
      Verifier shape varies by tier (assertion_only, unit, integration,
      reexecute); see <code>runlog-docs/12-stability-and-versioning.md</code>
      &sect;17.4 for the per-tier contract.{' '}
    </>
  )}
  The engine that promotes entries to <code>verified</code> ships in
  milestone <strong>M05</strong> &mdash; weighted usage telemetry plus
  dependency-manifest correlation. Unsigned submissions land today; once
  M05 ships, only verifier-signed entries become candidates for
  promotion. The architecture is end-to-end; the trust-score loop is
  staged.
</div>
